Sentencas: In order to reduce the cost of the manufacturing of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFC), and to enable metal supported cell fabrication, a new fabrication method called Reactive Spray Deposition Technology (RSDT) for direct deposition of the material onto ceramic or metal support for low temperature SOFC is currently being developed.
Titulo: Reactive Spray Deposition Technology - An one-step deposition technique for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell barrier layers

Sentencas: The present work describes the effect on the performance of a SOFC when a Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9(GDC) layer has been introduced as diffusion barrier layer between the yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte and the La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta (LSC) cathode.
Titulo: Reactive Spray Deposition Technology - An one-step deposition technique for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell barrier layers

Sentencas: The dense, thin and fully crystalline GDC films were directly applied by RSDT.
Titulo: Reactive Spray Deposition Technology - An one-step deposition technique for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell barrier layers

Sentencas: without any post-deposition heating or sintering step.
Titulo: Reactive Spray Deposition Technology - An one-step deposition technique for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell barrier layers

Sentencas: The quality of the film and performance of the cell prepared by RSDT was compared to a GDC blocking layer deposited by screen printing (SP) and then sintered.
Titulo: Reactive Spray Deposition Technology - An one-step deposition technique for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell barrier layers

Sentencas: The observed ohmic resistance of the ASC with a GDC layer deposited by RSDT is 0.24 Omega cm(2), which is close to the expected theoretical value of 0.17 Omega cm(2) for a 5-mu m thick 8 mol% yttria YSZ (8YSZ) electrolyte at 873 K. Crown Copyright (C) 2010
Titulo: Reactive Spray Deposition Technology - An one-step deposition technique for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell barrier layers
